###This study aimed to test if eco-friendly, artificial shelters impact vertebrate community assemblage. We hypothesized that artificial shelters positively impact the relationship of desert vertebrate species and offer similar microclimatic facilitative benefits to those of native shrub species in the face of anthropogenic climate change. We predicted:
###1)   Vertebrate community compositions are similar across shelters, shrubs, and open microsites.
###2)   The number of vertebrate animals that associate with shrubs and shelters is similar, and they are different from the open gap.
###3)   The number of vertebrate species that associate with shrubs and shelters is similar, and they are different from the open gap.
###4)   Vertebrate animals associate with shrubs and shelters more than open areas because they are cooler, more humid, and experience less direct solar radiation.

microclimate_animals_compiled<-merge(microclimate_summarized, animals_compiled, by = c("site_code", "microsite", "region", "year", "season"))

summary_data <- combined_rii_long %>%
  group_by(microsite, variable) %>%
  summarize(avg_value = mean(value),
            sd_value = sd(value))

ggplot(summary_data, aes(x = variable, y = avg_value, color = microsite)) +
  geom_point(position = position_dodge(width = 0.8), size = 3) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = avg_value - sd_value, ymax = avg_value + sd_value), 
                position = position_dodge(width = 0.8), width = 0.2) +
  labs(x = "", y = "RII", fill = "Microsite") +
  theme_minimal() + theme_classic() + coord_flip() + scale_x_discrete(labels = c("rii_abundance" = "Abundance", 
                              "rii_richness" = "Richness", 
                              "rii_evenness" = "Evenness")) + theme(text = element_text(size = 12), panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA, size = 1.5), axis.text = element_text(size = 12)) + theme(aspect.ratio = 1) + geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + labs(colour = "Microsite")

RII_winter<-read.csv("C:/Users/Nargol Ghazian/Desktop/PhD-Shelter-Shrub-Climate/shelters/global model files/RII_winter.csv")

combined_rii_long_winter <- RII_winter %>%
  gather(key = "variable", value = "value", rii_abundance, rii_richness, rii_evenness)
  
summary_data_winter <- combined_rii_long_winter %>%
  group_by(microsite, variable, site_code) %>%
  summarize(avg_value = mean(value),
            sd_value = sd(value))  
            
mod.rii.winter<-glm(avg_value~microsite%in% site_code+ as.factor(variable), data = summary_data_winter)
summary(mod.rii.winter)
